elements.2211.03208_00edd66487f833a95eda2eee6138b: Drug development is a wide scientific field that faces many challenges these days
elements.2211.03208_c88598c86e305019721baddb30a11: Among them are extremely high development costs, long development times, as well as a low number of new drugs that are approved each year
elements.2211.03208_88bd1313b3383d8bbeaa43be8c262: To solve these problems, new and innovate technologies are needed that make the drug discovery process of small-molecules more time and cost-efficient, and which allow to target previously undruggable target classes such as protein-protein interactions
elements.2211.03208_d0f93be314d972f0d80d1a19a24bf: Structure-based virtual screenings have become a leading contender in this context
elements.2211.03208_dd39daf8d1cc7846d94f7dd5f09e6: In this review, we give an introduction to the foundations of structure-based virtual screenings, and survey their progress in the past few years
elements.2211.03208_5dcc89c995e4ea4b005de3033e930: We outline key principles, recent success stories, new methods, available software, and promising future research directions
elements.2211.03208_23f6995342463f05ce134cf17c997: Virtual screenings have an enormous potential for the development of new small-molecule drugs, and are already starting to transform early-stage drug discovery.
elements.2211.03208_8b2d03e454e7bc67522d591de6622: drug discovery, structure-based virtual screenings, molecular docking, ultra-large libraries, machine learning, deep learning, GPU acceleration, free energy simulations
elements.2211.03208_aca2dccf69f0f41ed5f00f9d42cf6: The development of novel small-molecule drugs is a highly challenging process, which is time-consuming and expensive
elements.2211.03208_63eff0f37e5014dc9ba3dbe70151b: One critical step in this process is the discovery and optimization of hit and lead compounds
elements.2211.03208_b938d4811425ec1851cf2a10ba8a3: In the past few decades, experimental high-throughput screening (HTS) has been the primary method of discovering new hit compounds, and this approach is still the dominant method today
elements.2211.03208_f86d8659c8c7c2fb5553ea3003aab: However, HTSs often suffer from several major disadvantages and challenges:
elements.2211.03208_bb65db63651cd4e3a41b44fdae432: HTSs can be time-consuming, e.g. because the binding assays that will be used in the screen have to be prepared and optimized
elements.2211.03208_b689c777394b5f7f6f3f843aaea0d: The ligand library that will be screened has to be prepared as well
elements.2211.03208_6394fd1a158b2d2db355851cb54fe: The HTS itself can also be time-consuming, depending on the binding assays used and the equipment that is available to carry out the screen.
elements.2211.03208_7028be5298e9cad74470b4074a1cd: HTSs tend to be quite expensive, not least because of the robots that are needed to carry out the screens, as well as the physical ligand library
elements.2211.03208_f7bce49f240e23a6ed180a0cc4bdd: Initial hit compounds obtained by HTSs are often only moderately biologically active, which can in most cases be attributed to the fact that the screened libraries are of relatively small size (typically tens to hundreds of thousands of ligands).
elements.2211.03208_f51892cdc37fddc152a1dd2ff0b19: As hits obtained by HTSs usually do not lead to very high-affinity binders, challenging target sites, such as flat protein-protein interactions or allosteric sites, can often not be successfully targeted.
elements.2211.03208_ccc6558be912a04cde6a47bdfca5a: In HTSs that lead to sufficiently good hit compounds, the number of obtained hits and thus scaffolds are often quite limited
elements.2211.03208_018225ca8486e9e14b3085877e215: Furthermore, the same screening libraries (and thus scaffolds) are often used again and again in HTSs for different drug development campaigns, strongly limiting the chemical space of molecules that is explored for discovering new hit compounds.
elements.2211.03208_ef28d2b1a3be00766a94fd3f28aeb: HTSs typically do not take into account whether the discovered hits are specific to the targeted receptor or are possibly binding to other biological macromolecules as well.
elements.2211.03208_4dbde906faac0f6a705a01b88b3ca: HTSs do not provide mechanistic insight into how the ligands are binding to their target receptors
elements.2211.03208_69d81486bdfb597516836a527b482: In phenotypic kind of screens, it is typically not even known to which receptor the ligand is binding.
elements.2211.03208_9abe45bda0ca40fab5224b9c04318: Virtual screening approaches can mitigate all of the above problems, each to a different extent
elements.2211.03208_ec0ed49bbcf8a34ee9c4aba4fe22c: Virtual screenings can be very fast and cost-effective
elements.2211.03208_e2fc2c4e8ff9d58b4e62fd8dee52a: They can lead to highly potent initial hit compounds, and address even challenging target sites such as protein-protein interactions
elements.2211.03208_20f7006392353f5367430876caa29: In structure-based virtual screenings (SBVSs), the binding mode of the ligand to the target receptor is predicted, and thus (predicted) mechanistic insights are available
elements.2211.03208_7706d0228ba260b56bae7a9081ab6: Virtual screens can also lead to larger number of hit compounds with different scaffolds, thus providing a range of backup compounds.

elements.2211.03208_1d499cb3559f4f8e3b4547bf07e2b: Virtual screenings are procedures, in which a collection of ligands is computationally screened for their ability to bind to a given receptor structure
elements.2211.03208_f12ff111a3706d64bbbf1887d70c6: Receptors are most often proteins in the biomedical sciences but can be any type of biological macromolecule, including RNA or DNA
elements.2211.03208_c882234274eb3ae7b7cdfff10aaca: Virtual screens can be classified as ligand-based or structure-based
elements.2211.03208_2b91e61fba601575292f5388ab76b: In ligand-based virtual screens, only the structure of known active compounds is used for the screening procedure to identify new active compounds
elements.2211.03208_c6d57b100a63250fbcdd764ef1fa3: If the 3D structure of the receptor is available, structure-based methods can be used to carry out binding free energy calculations to estimate how strong the ligand binds to the targeted receptor, and the binding mode can be predicted as well
elements.2211.03208_4666daf2ac7c493ef801279d1121c: There are a large number of free energy methods, and because of their high speed, the predominant type used in virtual screens are molecular docking procedures
elements.2211.03208_fcca54e9c79a79e085a7bea9416ca: Structure-based virtual screenings are normally preferred over ligand-based screens when the goal is to identify novel scaffolds, since ligand-based approaches are often biased towards compounds similar to known binders and do not provide a docking pose
elements.2211.03208_edcf376aefa94122c3ee8daf56731: Virtual screens can be carried out in multiple stages, where in each subsequent step the best X compounds are used from the previous step, and methods of higher accuracy and/or computational are used to improve the quality of the dockings
elements.2211.03208_021c0e0548be7f524cb410946721a: This principle is illustrated in Figure
elements.2211.03208_299c045524c45bb12e6cc848815c4: , where each stage acts as a funnel.
elements.2211.03208_4c97352f89f8849698c629b61eece: A large variety of docking programs have been developed in the past several decades
elements.2211.03208_c3616f8d049a5d17db244544451fa: Docking programs typically consist of two components
elements.2211.03208_1f9d1dcd989d1a8126765d9bd2d63: First, a conformational search algorithm that explores the possible binding modes (conformation) of the ligand and the protein
elements.2211.03208_8723e8e9ad42b0f14a075a247338c: The second part is the scoring function, which assigns to each conformation a docking score that correlates with the predicted binding affinity
elements.2211.03208_2e3649d639926d026a58e4bab32e1: The binding mode with the best score is typically the winning and final docking pose
elements.2211.03208_52c287fec5a764ce36ee28c9e267a: Docking algorithms can be classified into four primary categories: Physics-based (also called force field-based), knowledge-based (also called potential of mean force-based), empirical (also called regression-based), and machine learning-based (also called descriptor-based) docking routines that vary in the methods they utilize
elements.2211.03208_e3a633752d977ef352f491bb43ea6: , we explore deep learning-based docking methods, which are a subclass of machine learning-based methods that have been developed only recently and can greatly speed up the docking procedures.
elements.2211.03208_6f75b012cabf3aa9778a473bedc85: Structure-based docking requires the receptor structure as input
elements.2211.03208_28814fb2f74548681fe397d38bf6e: One primary source for receptor structures is the Protein Data Bank (PDB,
elements.2211.03208_78d26f5aead5a03e3b0a2dd0860de: ), which is the largest database regarding experimentally determined protein structures
elements.2211.03208_4ea6c08be733e3b23984b05dc7f6a: Here, X-Ray crystallography, nuclear magnetic resonance (NMR), as well as cryo-electron microscopy (cryo-EM) are the primary experimental methods to determine the structures of biological macromolecules
elements.2211.03208_341ad7716eefc3d0d64d4bc268f65: Cryo-EM is the youngest of these techniques and has experienced tremendous progress regarding its capabilities and resolution
elements.2211.03208_b69f65843278cc5aa76103bcd4e9d: Recently, even atomic resolution has been achieved
elements.2211.03208_9f2ccebb04ee4d21924c64e954994: Cryo-EM is particularly powerful regarding the determination of larger protein complexes, and thus also for the identification of protein-protein interactions.
elements.2211.03208_9d4e33ffb5b0f45b8ee26ab6ab3e8: An alternative to experimentally determined structures is predicted structures
elements.2211.03208_00a3d913041ec28cdd8c9ee758163: structure prediction are the two primary types of prediction methods
elements.2211.03208_b4d523a4b7a364e228eaf16ebe439: Homology modeling uses a structure of a homologous protein that is known as a template.
elements.2211.03208_be922fbd7d285e458648be106dba7: structure prediction does not require such a template and can predict new structures from scratch
elements.2211.03208_b99e1a6a42209f18b666374a41cc0: Structure prediction, similar to cryo-EM, has experienced a breakthrough in the past few years
elements.2211.03208_b5ccb8017156ad20f68bfbd51511f: , the structure of almost every protein known has been predicted and made freely available in the AlphaFold Structure Database
elements.2211.03208_42fccbd12ae6fc95d09f82bfa00da: The AlphaFold Structure Database contains over 200 million protein structures
elements.2211.03208_fd9712b0e92dbbecd48bf130ae028: These recent developments in structure determination enable structure-based virtual screenings for almost any target protein.
elements.2211.03208_f03d6d3094bc614d6a564059b04d1: Virtual screenings require ligand libraries that are used for the screening procedure
elements.2211.03208_af67852c5a1cb1b7242fb03480396: In the case of structure-based virtual screenings, the ligands have to be in a ready-to-dock format
elements.2211.03208_0455b3ac71067b1786c4466049cfa: Preparing ligands into a ready-to-dock format typically starts from the SMILES format and involves generating stereoisomers, tautomerization states, predicting protonation states, computing the 3D coordinates of the ligands, and converting them into the target formats
elements.2211.03208_f148449fd60722165d4036f53fa59: The precise formats that are needed depend on the docking programs that are used
elements.2211.03208_097b6fb93c7564a55642d3f8a442a: Most docking programs require ligands in the PDBQT, PDB, MOL2, or SDF formats
elements.2211.03208_2c897e5a79ca15cd0569bff0349c8: In ligand-based approaches, the ligands can be given in line notation, such as the SMILES format that is mostly used
elements.2211.03208_6fc949f1c58c1777773050dea0ee0: However, sometimes 3D pharmacophore models are used in ligand-based screenings, in which case the ligands might need to be in a 3D format as well.
elements.2211.03208_6d20f13823a952f249b76535869d9: Ultra-large virtual screens have emerged as one of the most powerful virtual screening approaches to date
elements.2211.03208_3b4956f7c1591b0192fe66563b4af: Virtual screenings have historically been called ultra-large when over
elements.2211.03208_9b4bb9c1c6df97a256435a0be3233: 100 million compounds are screened (though what ultra-large means might change in the future as computational power and library sizes increase
elements.2211.03208_3735ec776c4236dfb173bedf7ad42: Several high-profile papers have been published in the last few years, including experimental validation, that have demonstrated the potential of this approach (see Section
elements.2211.03208_ab8bc691e3955e8b4f53c2a1420f7: Ultra-large virtual screenings have become possible in the past few years due to the recent advancements of multiple technologies and resources:
elements.2211.03208_9268e29cae0dbce44701e4f552b8a: In the last decade, the first ultra-large ligand libraries with over 100 million commercially available molecules have become available.
elements.2211.03208_180689304ed32b3d0d1a5d173c584: The capabilities of university computers clusters, national supercomputers, and commercial cloud computing infrastructures have improved substantially
elements.2211.03208_ff1c8e0a1437a795ad28b79194009: Through these computational resources, sufficient computational power has become available to the scientific communities to carry out ultra-large virtual screenings.
elements.2211.03208_52f938ca332cf61611120416c7b6e: , that can screen ultra-large ligand libraries using the above-mentioned computational resources, including cloud computing infrastructure, became freely available.
elements.2211.03208_7db08ad9fc83efa696e6a411368ba: We will review available compound libraries and software in the sections below.
elements.2211.03208_75d45cfbf72c6c2a9c5fc5c76d537: Ultra-large ligand libraries can be of different types
elements.2211.03208_40e1622410b0d5dd0a83821e57685: refers to the free availability of the ligand database without general commercial availability, while commercial libraries contain compounds that are commercially available for purchasing
elements.2211.03208_7de5916534611a9040effb3f21fde: Proprietary libraries on the other hand are generally not available for purchasing, and usually only available for internal use by the company that possesses the library
elements.2211.03208_cb0c0a15dc5986fb55471300c7d8c: Commercial libraries of ultra-large size contain mostly compounds that do not yet exist physically but can be synthesized efficiently on-demand, meaning upon ordering, by compound vendors with a certain success probability
elements.2211.03208_5d828b905ed58f9e6824e7052f0a9: These libraries are therefore also called on-demand libraries
elements.2211.03208_4465dbe57e79a2ee4e39316413e0c: Below we review ultra-large ligand libraries of public and commercial nature
elements.2211.03208_56a7c977f057a113fd4420fa237da: Details on some proprietary libraries can be found in
elements.2211.03208_3de5e5d26540971c29d3924965e27: Public virtual libraries can be useful and interesting because they allow to explore and test compounds via virtual screenings that are beyond current commercial availability, and with that vastly increase the chemical space that can be explored
elements.2211.03208_5922cc1e9670522b09e1d9830eeb4: Below we look at two types of these ultra-large public virtual libraries.
elements.2211.03208_35c903c95f82fe057554a22172b16: The Generated Databases (GDBs) by the Reymond Research Group likely were the first ligand libraries of ultra-large scale
elements.2211.03208_74f370f3d05f637aa45898a91755b: The GDB-11, containing all molecules with up to 11 atoms of type carbon, nitrogen, oxygen, and fluorine that satisfy certain valency, chemical stability, and synthetic accessibility criteria contained 110.9 million stereoisomers
elements.2211.03208_a9959ece70d841b452903f1422d22: Subsequently, additional GDB libraries were published
elements.2211.03208_3df4044b87a5a851fb24d7db64430: Among them are the GDB-13 containing molecules with up to 13 atoms resulting in 977 million molecules, as well as the GDB-17 with up to 17 atoms of the aforementioned atom types giving rise to 166 billion molecules
elements.2211.03208_ad1cf81c6aafe9ebe09c084b327d4: While these libraries are among the first of ultra-large size, one disadvantage is that these libraries are only available in the SMILES format
elements.2211.03208_0a1a2e3fad3f86b51bce6184a054e: Another disadvantage is that the compounds are not commercially available for direct purchasing
elements.2211.03208_0ddc681816c94f7d5b2ead0be6f74: Rather, custom synthesis of these molecules is mostly required, which is possible via commercial companies but can be expensive and time-consuming
elements.2211.03208_a5accd5e01f1b09b14ada643d9dea: To address this problem, GDBChEMBL has been created, a library that contains only compounds from the GDB-17 that are similar to molecules in ChEMBL
elements.2211.03208_d5283f917f382c754d9098e06b707: However, it is of relatively small size and only contains 10 million compounds
elements.2211.03208_e30e5f5ab3838dce521c615e4d510: A similar library, GDBMedChem, was created that contains 10 million compounds from the GDB-17
elements.2211.03208_88e57bc950f5bd184437d6b42754d: It only contains compounds favorable from a medicinal chemistry point of view.
elements.2211.03208_2d6499b6cb48936a6e0e1e790ed10: The KnowledgeSpace is another chemical space, which is similar to eXplore (see below), but more difficult to access in general
elements.2211.03208_594a5104481bc6aa91e67a2d5800d: Like eXplore, it is based on commercially available building blocks and reactions known from the literature
elements.2211.03208_ca4800d665f57392465a11eba4664: However, there is no commercial service available that readily provides these compounds
elements.2211.03208_7ef433f0bacb7db28689f6f23a865: molecules, this space might be the largest public library for drug discovery available

elements.2211.03208_b72afbec2389735b78da2e53553d8: Ultra-large commercial libraries are based on a smaller number of fragments and combinatorial chemistry, which allows combining of the fragments via combinatorial chemistry to complete molecules
elements.2211.03208_8588b8399637ce1384b3648f2cfcc: One important aspect regarding these on-demand libraries is their chemical diversity
elements.2211.03208_2b50821594a324858eff64144d9b3: Combinatorial libraries like these might lead to large numbers of compounds, but do the resulting compounds also represent a diverse chemical space, rather than a small region in the chemical space with highly similar compounds? Two recent studies have looked into this question
elements.2211.03208_af9b3b6d3e24f1580b5645c701c54: They concluded that the resulting chemical spaces are surprisingly diverse and more diverse than typical physical HTS libraries
elements.2211.03208_3602d31b2837efcf23694ab96eed8: Below we review the major ultra-large on-demand libraries that are available.
elements.2211.03208_7c29e87fbde86cbe29df064f65eb6: The two major disadvantages of the GDBs, non-commercial availability and non-ready-to-dock format were first addressed by the ZINC libraries
elements.2211.03208_6ba7595bbc191a3707b857e0d3e91: ZINC15 (published in the year 2015) was the first ultra-large ligand library of commercially available compounds in a ready-to-dock format, with initially approximately 120 million compounds
elements.2211.03208_53a5d3e7e6f3e0d4ee7b5e4f716fa: The library has steadily grown since then and has reached approximately 1.5 billion molecules to date, out of which approximately 750 million are in a ready-to-dock format

elements.2211.03208_281fd4300a5600795252de91b7d67: DEEP LEARNING APPROACHES TO MOLECULAR DOCKING
elements.2211.03208_74409aeb07b2cdf8313dd377bbceb: Machine learning-based docking programs are one of the four types of docking programs, and they use a relatively large number of descriptors
elements.2211.03208_6a80144c07d55923578d66c6ce37c: Like empirical docking programs, machine learning-based docking programs need training on data
elements.2211.03208_c08b98ef29a248700973d4ee14771: Even though empirical scoring functions can be considered to be machine learning-based as well (e.g. because they often use multivariate linear regression), they use parameterized functions, whereas the term machine learning-based docking programs refer to nonparametric methods that can select the final functional form
elements.2211.03208_95600693372c284d62d04ff28cf09: Machine learning-based docking programs have a much larger number of descriptors (variables) than empirical docking methods
elements.2211.03208_4ca1dafeb60eddc851c2c2307da8c: The first machine learning methods for molecular docking appeared around 2004
elements.2211.03208_975b028ccec1e768ec2dec2e8e29a: Deep learning is a subdivision of machine learning, and in the past few years, the first deep learning approaches have been developed for molecular docking
elements.2211.03208_b68b17b2c0fa4ec10243566a81788: One advantage of deep learning approaches is that they can be orders of magnitude faster compared to classical docking programs
elements.2211.03208_dd1953d90c0bfeacb5ebe4f93bb62: High computational speeds become crucial when processing large ligand datasets, implying that deep learning methods can be particularly beneficial for screening ultra-large libraries
elements.2211.03208_db2d535fb400b3f5206dfd4d91f75: Apart from considerations of speed, deep learning methods have the potential to become more accurate in the future in terms of their accuracy regarding the predicted binding affinity and the predicted docking pose than traditional docking programs
elements.2211.03208_dc4d878536121939bc30c7afe97f3: In this section, we give an overview of deep learning approaches related to molecular docking
elements.2211.03208_a91a11b1bef5a2b8acda484c6708b: Docking programs predict the binding pose of a ligand to a protein, along with a score that characterizes the strength of the interaction
elements.2211.03208_64ea1878cb55de41ac559604dc481: Historically, deep learning-based scoring functions were developed first, while the first pose-prediction methods utilizing deep learning appeared only recently
elements.2211.03208_9f8ccac3a0a8d4ffd4436d5f1d7c5: Deep learning-based scoring functions are regression models that utilize known datasets of ligand-protein interaction pairs to predict the strength of an interaction by assigning a score
elements.2211.03208_305a5c8d500f4505108f345fea983: New deep learning-based docking programs that include both scoring and pose prediction are still very rare
elements.2211.03208_a8fc8c6ac8f008230cb6bd438e207: However, deep learning-based scoring functions and pose prediction methods can be combined into a full docking program, due to their modularity
elements.2211.03208_faed7aad4a1656c7571d5e01bc478: Here, a deep learning-based scoring function can for instance be used to score the binding poses obtained by a deep learning-based pose-prediction method
elements.2211.03208_1bb45eadd372b6cc94b26128f67f9: Alternatively, a deep learning-based scoring function can be used in combination with existing docking programs to (re)rank the docking poses generated by the existing docking program by reevaluating the generated conformations by the new scoring function
elements.2211.03208_4a534097ae61ea5a0bb68d9111c3c: A third possibility is to combine the deep learning-based scoring functions with existing sampling methods, where the scoring function is used as the cost function that is minimized during the optimization procedure
elements.2211.03208_1fbf02e279e8d683cf5489b03009a: The new docking methods can be used in ultra-large virtual screenings, e.g. with VirtualFlow, which already supports some of the new deep learning-based methods out of the box
elements.2211.03208_0ce3f788a8bd7353b43d8466a9737: This can, in principle, lead to substantial speed-ups compared to the deployment of traditional docking programs in virtual screening campaigns.
elements.2211.03208_d1330ad1905fc7bb9644df2179cde: A wide variety of deep learning-based scoring functions have been developed in the past several years
elements.2211.03208_ab0e79cd0d628b06ffc546d34566e: Here in this section, we look at pure scoring functions that were published without a sampling algorithm
elements.2211.03208_1cffa750b4383837ab4afbac0b61c: To our knowledge, historically one of the first such methods was NNScore 2.0
elements.2211.03208_eb1b25bb945e8c56950db3ff9393b: Later, a large number of other deep learning-based scoring functions have been developed

elements.2211.03208_e7d0666a9a2764075aa50cfd0db30: Here, free energy simulations based on molecular dynamics (MD) simulations can be used to improve the accuracy of the binding affinity estimates for the best compounds of the previous stage
elements.2211.03208_61748e109f4b38997a49b54544193: Free energy simulations are in theory exact (relative to the force field used), provided that the free energy converges (for that the simulations need to run long enough)
elements.2211.03208_9d64ddf56bbdd74b00f67789d7c84: They take into account the full dynamics of the molecular system, can treat all solvent molecules explicitly, and include all enthalpic and entropic components of the free energy
elements.2211.03208_522b29d88c0a3f3e8364d88b85482: When applied to a larger number of systems in an automated way, free energy simulations are also referred to as high-throughput free energy simulations (HTFESs)
elements.2211.03208_cedabd3ed5ca65d8ccce356a2d72f: In addition, quantum mechanics/molecular mechanics (QM/MM) methods can be used to treat the parts of the system (typically the ligand, the binding site of the protein, and possibly some solvent molecules at the binding site) with higher accuracy
elements.2211.03208_792199f569f8fbb1f210bdc157062: This can for example be beneficial if metals are located at the binding site of the protein or part of the ligand
elements.2211.03208_806d0c2be206f8ce65c7e3012bcc3: Hardware acceleration, in particular the usage of GPUs, is key regarding HTFESs

elements.2211.03208_bba70b00a3000f065efb11ed916a1: Structure-based virtual screenings have evolved into a powerful tool for drug discovery in the past few years
elements.2211.03208_a4501ac1c4ba6d413bd3916814622: Ultra-large virtual screens allow to access billions of compounds, allowing to find exceptionally tight-fitting ligands for even highly challenging target sites
elements.2211.03208_9c07d79d15d07aa744c11860aeeb0: This approach allows to drug new target classes such as allosteric sites or protein-protein interactions, which with approximately 500,000 types are considered to be one of the holy grails of drug discovery
elements.2211.03208_47b872f4910a591bc95c868901c9d: Machine learning and deep learning techniques on the molecular docking and virtual screening levels allow to speed up the calculations by orders of magnitude, as do other algorithmic approaches such as synthon-based methods, or the use of hardware accelerators such as GPUs
elements.2211.03208_a708929a75aeec172d711b6adde7e: It is expected that virtual screenings will further expand the accessed chemical space by orders of magnitude in the coming years, with no limits in sight given the vastness of the chemical space of molecules suitable for drug discovery
elements.2211.03208_7e1ed2a8514bbd322f7ba9aecb598: Deep learning approaches for molecular docking and for free energy simulations have the potential to significantly improve the accuracy and reliability of free energy predictions, though significant works lies still ahead to achieve this goal
elements.2211.03208_86ef4678563816269514d30b5e02a: GPUs and other hardware accelerators will aid in accessing larger regions of the chemical space of druglike molecules in the future
elements.2211.03208_3d2b3fe4a826a2a537a526234059d: GPUs will be key for achieving highly accurate free energy simulations, whether on the classical or the quantum level, which hold great promise to improve the reliability of binding affinity prediction
elements.2211.03208_977192c43aee61329945e44edaf9a: In addition, structure-based virtual screens can be extended to tasks other than hit and lead discovery and optimization, such as predicting off-target binding via inverse virtual screenings or combining them with the prediction of pharmacokinetic properties
elements.2211.03208_ff99a485c19027f523613db979167: In summary, structure-based virtual screens are on the one hand already a mature technique, and able to be routinely applied in drug discovery campaigns to identify potent hit and lead compounds and to optimize them
elements.2211.03208_2017b0f8708ec60f0171c2f2cb25e: On the other hand, they have only recently become powerful enough to be of real value in actual drug discovery projects, and have barely begun to scratch the surface of what they can achieve in the future
elements.2211.03208_90a2a4e7effdb9f3819f19875fccb: A bright future therefore likely lies ahead for structure-based virtual screens.
elements.2211.03208_507c62438ba3e87897e8e225f9991: Early-stage drug discovery using traditional methods such as experimental high-throughput screens faces several major problems, such as high costs, labor, and poor initial hit compounds
elements.2211.03208_4d77e27457ea242ae88b5190a3d50: Structure-based virtual screenings can solve most of these problems, by reducing the costs and workload, and by improving the quality of hit as well as lead compounds.
elements.2211.03208_8eafbe8b1206f0398048cd015d0df: Ultra-large structure-based virtual screenings in particular have proven to be able to discover highly potent hit and lead compounds, as well as to optimize initial hit compounds
elements.2211.03208_3618e637f3a65bf0f29e7f50ac99b: This in turn leads to the ability to find potent binders to more challenging target classes such as protein-protein interactions.
